HTML

# add script to html
-> <script src="script_name.js"></script>

# add style to html
-> <link href="style_name.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">

#add label and input to html
-> <label for=""id_name">"Text here"</label>
-> <input type="what type text we enter here" id="where to add this text"<br><br>

#add button to html
-> <button onclick="script_name()>"Some text"</button><br><br>
<div id='result'></div>

#add image to html
-> <img scr="image_name.jpg"> => can set "width/height" <img scr="name" width="250" height="200">
If image can show on display we can print a message => <img src="name" alt="black gun"

#declare language of page
<html lang="en">

#Title attribute
<p title="I'm a tooltip"> Enter some text here.</p> => when mouse is on text will show "title text"

# Paragraphs <p>

-> The browser will automatically remove any extra spaces and lines when the page is displayed

-> horizontal rules (make line) <hr>
-> break lines <br>
If we use <br> in between <p> text will separate it

<pre> Element
-> text inside a <pre> element is displayed in a fixed-width font(Courier)
